cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about building a POS Tagger for Kannada language using machine learning and neural network models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of different modeling techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper explores the use of character and word embeddings, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of POS tagging for named entity recognition, which could also place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
